The paper deals with covert communication, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the manipulation of packet timings and contents, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of an M/M/1 queue and service rate also suggests a networking and internet architecture focus (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a construction for covert communication, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or systems and control (cs.SY) depending on the specific implementation.
